<headline>Dense Fog Advisory issued September 12 at 5:49AM EDT until September 12 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EDT THIS MORNING...
* WHAT...Visibility less than one mile in dense fog.
* WHERE...Rockbridge, Amherst, Pittsylvania, Campbell,
Appomattox, Buckingham, Halifax and Charlotte Counties.
* WHEN...Until 9 AM EDT this morning.
* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Calm winds, a very humid air mass, and wet
ground from recent rainfall has promoted the development of
widespread dense fog throughout the Piedmont and the southern
Shenandoah Valley. Visibility will be as low as 1/4 to 1/2 mile
in many locations this morning, especially in valleys, and near
bodies of water such as rivers and lakes.</description>
<instruction>If you are planning to travel early this morning, reduce speed,
leave extra space between you and the vehicle in front of you,
allow extra time to reach your destination, and use your low beam
headlights.
Conditions are expected to begin to improve after 9 AM EDT this
morning.</instruction>
